# React Rules

## Project Initialization
```bash
npm create vite@latest md-project-name -- --template react-ts
cd md-project-name
npm install
npm install react-router-dom
npm install -D tailwindcss @tailwindcss/vite
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Required Libraries — Use These, Not Alternatives
| Purpose | Library |
|---------|---------|
| Routing | React Router DOM |
| Server state, data fetching, caching | TanStack Query (React Query) |
| Global client UI state | Zustand |
| Forms + validation | React Hook Form + Zod |
| HTTP client | Axios (not native fetch) |
| Date utilities | date-fns (import only needed functions) |
| Icons | Lucide React |

## UI Standards
- **shadcn/ui** as the starting point for all UI elements — buttons, forms, dialogs, tables, etc.
- **Tailwind CSS** for all styling — no raw CSS or CSS-in-JS unless there is no other option
- Customize components via Tailwind classes and direct source edits — never override with external CSS
- Never override or remove accessibility attributes on shadcn/ui components
- Apply Molecular Designs brand colors and typography through `tailwind.config.ts`

## Project Structure
```
src/
  components/        # Shared/reusable UI components
    ui/              # shadcn/ui components (generated)
  features/          # Feature-specific modules (components, hooks, utils per feature)
  hooks/             # Shared custom hooks
  lib/               # Utility functions, API client, constants
  pages/             # Route-level page components
  types/             # Shared TypeScript types and interfaces
  App.tsx
  main.tsx
```

## Data Fetching
- Use TanStack Query for all server state — **no custom useEffect fetch logic**
- Use Axios for all HTTP calls — configure a shared Axios instance in `src/lib/api.ts`
- Use Zod schemas for API response validation and form validation

## Error Handling
- **React Error Boundaries** required at all route-level components — never let rendering errors show a blank screen
- User-facing error messages must be actionable and non-technical — never expose stack traces or internal error details
- Use TanStack Query's built-in error states or try/catch for async errors

## Responsive Design (required on every UI)
- Test at minimum widths: 375px (mobile), 768px (tablet), 1280px (desktop)
- Use Tailwind responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- Navigation collapses to hamburger menu or drawer on mobile
- Tables scroll horizontally or reflow to cards on small screens
- Touch targets minimum 44×44px

## State Management
- **TanStack Query** for anything that comes from the server
- **Zustand** for global UI state that does not come from the server
- Local `useState` for component-local state
- Do not use Redux unless the project has exceptionally complex state needs — document the reason

## Performance
- Target Core Web Vitals: LCP < 2.5s, INP < 200ms, CLS < 0.1
- Use Lighthouse for audits
- Import date-fns functions individually — never `import * from 'date-fns'`

## Deployment
- Internal apps: deployed per organization standards (e.g. development servers via GitHub Actions, VPN access)
- Public/AWS apps: S3 + CloudFront (static), ECS (containerized), Lambda (serverless)
- Environment-specific config via GitHub Actions Secrets and `.env.example`
